# Firebase Admin SDK Configuration (for server-side operations like uploads)
# Get these from your Firebase Project Settings > Service Accounts > Generate new private key
# IMPORTANT: For the private key, copy the entire string including "-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----" and "-----END PRIVATE KEY-----".
# In your hosting provider (like Vercel), you can paste the multi-line key directly.
# In a .env.local file, you must wrap it in quotes like this: FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\nYourKeyHere\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"
FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL="firebase-adminsdk-.....@your-project-id.iam.gserviceaccount.com"
FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\nYOUR_PRIVATE_KEY_HERE\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"
